          <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl bg-teal-600 px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold text-center">Check In</div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-gray-500">Put this on a tablet in your waiting room</p>
      </div>
      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-teal-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 1.5H8.25A2.25 2.25 0 006 3.75v16.5a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25h7.5A2.25 2.25 0 0018 20.25V3.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H13.5m-3 0V3h3V1.5m-3 0h3m-3 18.75h3" /></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Self-check-in that eliminates the front desk bottleneck</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Patients enter their phone number on a tablet. That's it. No clipboards, no forms, no standing in line. Your front desk staff goes from traffic cop to patient advocate.</p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-400">Works on any tablet or phone. No app installation required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 3: Calendar -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-teal-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6.75 3v2.25M17.25 3v2.25M3 18.75V7.5a2.25 2.25 0 012.25-2.25h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0121 7.5v11.25m-18 0A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0021 18.75m-18 0v-7.5A2.25 2.25 0 015.25 9h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0121 11.25v7.5" /></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Every calendar. Every EHR. One sync.</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Your providers use different tools — and that's fine. Schedulite connects to Google Calendar, Outlook, Apple Calendar, Epic, Athena, Calendly, and 10+ more. Everyone stays in their flow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-8">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3">
          <% ["Google Calendar", "Outlook 365", "Apple Calendar", "Epic", "Athena", "Calendly", "Cal.com", "Jane App", "NexHealth"].each do |name| %>
